      }
    ],
    "overview": "## feats CLI and runner test coverage — Difficulty: 2/5\n\nThis PR adds end-to-end and unit test coverage for the `feats` BDD runner with no production code changes. It exercises three layers: `parseArgs`/`runFeatsCli` (argument parsing, exit codes, meta flags, glob resolution, tag filtering), `runCore` (structured summary, reporter event ordering, lifecycle hooks, world factory), and the newly exported `runScenarioPure` (background steps, Before/After hook ordering, tag-filtered hooks, step skipping after failure). The CLI tests scaffold temp projects on disk, monkeypatch `process.stdout/stderr.write` to capture output, and assert on exit codes and emitted text.\n\n```mermaid\nflowchart TD\n    A[parseArgs argv] --> B{flags valid?}\n    B -- no --> C[throw CliError exit=2]\n    B -- yes --> D[runFeatsCli]\n    D --> E[resolveRequires glob steps]\n    D --> F[loadFeatures glob]\n    E --> G[runCore features]\n    F --> G\n    G --> H[runScenarioPure per scenario]\n    H --> I[reporters: onStart..onStep..onEnd]\n    G --> J[summary + exitCode]\n    J --> K[process exit]\n```\n\nRiskiest area to watch: the global `process.stdout/stderr.write` reassignment shared across many tests — if `runFeatsCli` throws before the `finally` restore in any helper, or if bun:test runs these concurrently, capture state can leak between tests and produce flaky or cross-contaminated output assertions.",
